          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1717669219636-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the<strong> </strong>linguine is cooked, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium-low heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced garlic </strong>and cook for 30 secs or until it starts to sizzle slightly</p><p>Add the <strong>torn smoked mackerel</strong> and cook for 1 min further</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1717669223812-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1717669223812-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1717669223812-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1717669223812-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1717669223812-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> drained linguine </strong>and<strong> </strong>a few splashes of the <strong>reserved starchy pasta water</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> then increase the heat to high</p><p>Add your <strong>soft cheese </strong>and cook for 1-2 min, stirring until everything is combined and the sauce begins to stick to the pasta</p><p>Tip: Add a splash more starchy pasta water if the sauce is looking a little dry</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1717669227370-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1717669227370-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1717669227370-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1717669227370-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1717669227370-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Squeeze in the juice of the <strong>remaining lemon</strong> and add <strong>half </strong>your<strong> grated Italian hard cheese</strong> (you'll use the rest later) with<strong> half</strong> the<strong> chopped dill </strong>and<strong> chives</strong> (save the rest for garnish!)</p><p>Give everything a good mix up and season with a generous grind of <strong>pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>smoked mackerel gluten free linguine</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1717669234461-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1717669234461-x400.jpg",
